<paragraph blockId="5.[151,543,151,177]" box="[151,543,151,177]" pageId="5" pageNumber="583">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,543,151,177]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="5" pageNumber="583" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,543,151,177]" pageId="5" pageNumber="583">
Genus 
<taxonomicName authority="McLachlan 1877" authorityName="McLachlan" authorityYear="1877" box="[238,543,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Leptoceridae" genus="Oecetis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="583" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[238,326,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="583">Oecetis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="McLachlan, R." box="[334,543,151,177]" pageId="5" pageNumber="583" pagination="281 - 348" refId="ref6267" refString="McLachlan, R. (1877) A Monographic Revision and Synopsis of the Trichoptera of the European Fauna. Part VI. Van Voorst, London, pp. 281 - 348, plates xxxii - xxxvii." type="book chapter" year="1877">McLachlan 1877</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="583" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,223,286]" pageId="5" pageNumber="583">
This is a very large genus with worldwide distribution, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="McLachlan" authorityYear="1877" box="[804,888,224,250]" class="Insecta" family="Leptoceridae" genus="Oecetis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="583" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[804,888,224,250]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="583">Oecetis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is represented in the Neotropics by 51 species (
<bibRefCitation author="Holzenthal, R. W. &amp; Calor, A. R." box="[159,449,259,285]" pageId="5" pageNumber="583" pagination="1 - 566" refId="ref5887" refString="Holzenthal, R. W. &amp; Calor, A. R. (2017) Catalog of the Neotropical Trichoptera (Caddisflies). Zookeys, 654, 1 - 566. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 654.9516" type="journal article" year="2017">Holzenthal &amp; Calor 2017</bibRefCitation>
). In 
<collectingCountry box="[498,590,260,286]" name="Panama" pageId="5" pageNumber="583">Panama</collectingCountry>
, nine species are known. Herein we add one more species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
